title: Regal 33 Express - Express Cruiser

description: The Forte gelcoat (your choice of two colors) perfectly accentuates the sporty silhouette of this boat. Its contours are further enhanced by Crownline’s patented F.A.S.T. Tab hull design which not only embraces the distinctive “sports car” styling of the 215 SS, but also ensures a safe and comfortable ride by increasing planning efficiency and stability in high speed turns. The transom walk through has a filler cushion to preserve the comfortable, full length sun bed area that is so important for relaxing and catching some rays. The super sport cockpit seating features driver and passenger bucket seats with flip-up bolsters. The rear bench seat is hinged to access the finished storage area beneath. The deep hull design is really evident upon entering the spacious bow area. And the seating is exceptionally comfortable, with 16-degree lean backs, pillow top cushioning and STANDARD duty flip-up armrests. There’s tons of storage throughout the boat – even for your wakeboards and skis. They stow away under the portside and starboard bow seats. The 215 SS comes standard with a deluxe Heritage tandem axle trailer with a swing tongue and color matched to your boat.
title: Crownline 215 SS

description:
ACOA was built at Double & Jesse in Germany to a design of Ed Dubois.
With an aluminium hull designed to cross oceans, Acoa completed a round-the-world trip and a passage in the Antarctic.

Extremely well maintained, Acoa underwent her first refit in 2005 at Orams Marine in New Zealand.
More recently all the paintwork has been redone in Awlgrip and the superstructure repainted in 2017.
Acoa's ongoing maintenance programme has also included all electronic systems being upgraded in 2019.
A second scheduled world tour has been cancelled due to changed circumstances, but anytime Acoa is ready to go on a long journey again.

Manufacturer Provided Description

MY 44… Call her now… MY6

The MY6 captures the essence of Fountaine Pajot Motor Yachts promise: to widen your horizons.

With a length of 15 metres, the Motor Yacht MY6 has two steering positions in the saloon or on the flybridge. With its dual engines of up to 2 x 353 Kw and 2 x 480 hp, its power output promises you the emotions of dynamic sailing with the benefit of an extremely stable structure, even at high speeds. Equipped with the Volvo 500 or 650 IPS system, the MY6 makes manoeuvring easier with the ability to move laterally with a simple push of the joystick. You keep control of its power in all circumstances.

Our designer, PierAngelo Andreani, has developed extraordinary volumes for the MY6 equivalent to those that a 20-metre monohull would offer. The living space on board, evocative of a holiday home, is simply breathtaking: its huge flybridge offers a superb view on the horizon, its saloon, an actual loft with its own terrace, boasts a spacious lounge and a kitchen that opens directly onto the cockpit.

 

The MY6 is remarkable for the seamless circulation between inside and outside. In the passageway, the private spaces, all with a full view of the sea, combine intimacy and pleasure: an impressively sized Owner’s Suite on the port side, two VIP bedrooms on the starboard side and an optional cabin at the front, (otherwise used as storage spaces). The Motor Yacht MY6 is set to satisfy your wildest demands for the highest level of comfort. The aesthetics designed by PierAngelo Andreani is captivating with its modern lines, blending beautiful materials, and definitely makes the MY6 an essential reference in the Motor Yacht world.

The MY6 is available with an Owners suite and its ensuite bathroom, two double cabins each with ensuite bathroom.

The MY6 offers unique technical specificities and sleek lines, enhanced by the sophistication of life on board.

Boston Whaler 16’ Sakonnet, 1976

This classic Whaler was the last Sakonnet to receive the optional mahogany; the factory had just ended the mahogany option, but the Himel Marine had a customer whom insisted, so Boston Whaler built the last one for him.   

This boat is solid and was stored inside a garage for 40+ years when not being used. title: Nautitech 47 Power

description:
The 210 BR represents a bold approach in hull design. We've kept the time proven great ride of the 19 degree dead rise hull, but we've added a lifting pad to the bottom and an integrated jack plate to the transom. Now you can have it all with improved performance, fuel economy, and a great ride, and as a bonus it even sports a bit less draft. The improved hull isn't all you get. The interior has been tweaked and squeezed to get everything a serious fisherman could ask for such as space for 10 7-foot plus rods in the lockable rod boxes, dual live wells, spacious front and rear deck, under gunwale molded in rod racks, and believe it or not, a potty room under the console. Yes, this is a family friendly bay boat as well with features such as fold away jump seats in the rear deck, and generous cup holders throughout. More pictures coming!! Boat is in excellent condition.
